-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, Est Media Shares Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-06-08T15:29:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-est-media-shares-move-in-budapest.html
The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index rose 0.2
percent to 17,019.75 by the close in Budapest, extending its
gain this week to 3.9 percent.  The following are among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  ,  Hungary ’s largest lender, dropped
as much as 1.6 percent and last traded 0.2 percent lower at
3,400 forint. Hungary’s economy contracted for the first time in
more than two years in the first quarter, statistical data
showed today.  Est Media Nyrt. (ESTMEDIA HB), a Hungarian entertainment
company, gained for a third day, the longest winning streak
since November, after saying on June 6 that it plans to issue
three-year convertible bonds for a unit that organizes music
festivals. The shares jumped 4.4 percent to 48 forint, bringing
their advance in the past three days to 37 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
